 Weather SA forecaster Wayne Venter said the wind gusts were at 305 kilometers per hour.  “The storm is smaller than Idai, but more intense. We are expecting more rain and more damage during this storm.” ALSO READ: Children bear the brunt in the aftermath of Cyclone Idai He added that the storm is expected to be the strongest cyclone to ever hit the Mozambican and southern Tanzanian coast. The cyclone is expected to make landfall in the district of Palma. Heavy rains for the next four days are also expected in Nacala, Memba, Erati, Namapa, Mozambique Island, Mussoril and Monapo districts in the province of Nampula, northern Mozambique. ALSO READ: To Buzi and back home – Tereasa Dias’ last day in Mozambique